h8601.definition: from {{h644}}; cookery, i.e. (concretely) a cake; baked piece.

h8602.definition: from an unused root meaning to smear; plaster (as gummy) or slime; (figuratively) frivolity; foolish things, unsavoury, untempered.

h8603.definition: from the same as {{h8602}}; quagmire; Tophel, a place near the Desert; Tophel.

h8604.definition: from the same as {{h8602}}; frivolity; folly, foolishly.

h8605.definition: from {{h6419}}; intercession, supplication; by implication, a hymn; prayer.

h8607.definition: from {{h6452}}; ford; Tiphsach, a place in Mesopotamia; Tipsah.

h8608.definition: a primitive root; to drum, i.e. play (as) on the tambourine; taber, play with timbrels.

h8609.definition: a primitive root; to sew; (women that) sew (together).

h8610.definition: a primitive root; to manipulate, i.e. seize; chiefly to capture, wield, specifically, to overlay; figuratively, to use unwarrantably; catch, handle, (lay, take) hold (on, over), stop, × surely, surprise, take.

h8611.definition: from the base of {{h8608}}; a smiting, i.e. (figuratively) contempt; tabret.

h8612.definition: the same as {{h8611}}; Topheth, a place near Jerusalem; Tophet, Topheth.

h8613.definition: probably a form of {{h8612}}; Tophteh, a place of cremation; Tophet.

h8614.definition: (Aramaic) perhaps from {{h8199}}; judicial, i.e. a lawyer; sheriff.

h8615.definition: from {{h6960}}; (compare {{h6961}}); literally a cord (as an attachment); figuratively, expectancy; expectation(-ted), hope, live, thing that I long for.

h8616.definition: the same as {{h8615}}; Tikvah, the name of two Israelites; Tikvah.

h8618.definition: from {{h6965}}; an opponent; rise up against.

h8619.definition: from {{h8628}} (in the musical sense); a trumpet; trumpet.

h8620.definition: a form of {{h8619}}; Tekoa, a place in Palestine; Tekoa, Tekoah.

h8621.definition: or תְּקֹעִי; patronymically from {{h8620}}; a Tekoite or inhabitant of Tekoah; Tekoite.

h8622.definition: or תְּקֻפָה; from {{h5362}}; a revolution, i.e. (of the sun) course, (of time) lapse; circuit, come about, end.

h8625.definition: (Aramaic) corresponding to {{h8254}}; to balance; Tekel, be weighed.

h8626.definition: a primitive root; to equalize, i.e. straighten (intransitive or transitive); figuratively, to compose; set in order, make straight.

h8627.definition: (Aramaic) corresponding to {{h8626}}; to straighten up, i.e. confirm; establish.

h8628.definition: a primitive root; to clatter, i.e. slap (the hands together), clang (an instrument); by analogy, to drive (a nail or tent-pin, a dart, etc.); by implication, to become bondsman by handclasping); blow (a trumpet), cast, clap, fasten, pitch (tent), smite, sound, strike, × suretiship, thrust.

h8629.definition: from {{h8628}}; a blast of a trumpet; sound.

h8630.definition: a primitive root; to overpower; prevail (against).

h8631.definition: (Aramaic) corresponding to {{h8630}}; to become (causatively, make) mighty or (figuratively) obstinate; make firm, harden, be(-come) strong.

h8633.definition: from {{h8630}}; might or (figuratively) positiveness; authority, power, strength.

h8634.definition: probably for {{h8653}}; a reeling; Taralah, a place in Palestine; Taralah.

h8636.definition: from {{h7235}}; multiplication, i.e. percentage or bonus in addition to principal; increase, unjust gain.

h8637.definition: a denominative from {{h7270}}; to cause to walk; teach to go.

h8638.definition: a denominative from {{h7275}} in the sense of throwing over; to transfer, i.e. translate; interpret.

h8639.definition: from {{h7290}}; a lethargy or (by implication) trance; deep sleep.

h8640.definition: of foreign derivation; Tirhakah, a king of Kush; Tirhakah.

h8641.definition: or תְּרֻמָה; (Deuteronomy 12:11), from {{h7311}}; a present (as offered up), especially in sacrifice or as tribute; gift, heave offering (shoulder), oblation, offered(-ing).

h8642.definition: formed as {{h8641}}; a sacrificial offering; oblation.

h8643.definition: from {{h7321}}; clamor, i.e. acclamation of joy or a battle-cry; especially clangor of trumpets, as an alarum; alarm, blow(-ing) (of, the) (trumpets), joy, jubile, loud noise, rejoicing, shout(-ing), (high, joyful) sound(-ing).

h8644.definition: from {{h7322}} in the sense of its congener {{h7495}}; a remedy; medicine.

h8645.definition: probably from {{h7329}}; a species of tree (apparently from its slenderness), perhaps the cypress; cypress.

h8646.definition: of uncertain derivation; Terach, the father of Abraham; also a place in the Desert; Tarah, Terah.

h8647.definition: of uncertain derivation; Tirchanah, an Israelite; Tirhanah.

h8648.definition: (Aramaic) feminine תַּרְתֵּין; corresponding to {{h8147}}; two; second,   twelve, two.

h8649.definition: and תַּרְמוּת; or תַּרְמִית; from {{h7411}}; fraud; deceit(-ful), privily.

h8650.definition: probably for {{h766}}; a pole (as a mast or flagstaff); beacon, mast.

h8651.definition: (Aramaic) corresponding to {{h8179}}; a door; by implication, a palace; gate mouth.

h8654.definition: patrial from an unused name meaning gate; a Tirathite or inhabitant of an unknown Tirah; Tirathite.

h8655.definition: plural from {{h7495}}; a healer; Teraphim (singular or plural) a family idol; idols(-atry), images, teraphim.

h8656.definition: from {{h7521}}; delightsomeness; Tirtsah, a place in Palestine; also an Israelitess; Tirzah.

h8657.definition: of foreign derivation; Teresh, a eunuch of Xerxes; Teresh.

h8658.definition: probably of foreign derivation (compare {{h8659}}); a gem, perhaps the topaz; beryl.

h8659.definition: probably the same as {{h8658}} (as the region of the stone, or the reverse); Tarshish, a place on the Mediterranean, hence, the ephithet of a merchant vessel (as if for or from that port); also the name of a Persian and of an Israelite; Tarshish, Tharshish.

h8660.definition: of foreign derivation; the title of a Persian deputy or governor; Tirshatha.

h8661.definition: of foreign derivation; Tartan, an Assyrian; Tartan.

h8662.definition: of foreign derivation; Tartak, a deity of the Avvites; Tartak.

h8663.definition: from {{h7722}}; a crashing or loud clamor; crying, noise, shouting, stir.

h8664.definition: patrial from an unused name meaning recourse; a Tishbite or inhabitant of Tishbeh (in Gilead); Tishbite.

h8666.definition: or תְּשֻׁבָה; from {{h7725}}; a recurrence (of time or place); a reply (as returned); answer, be expired, return.

h8667.definition: from {{h7760}}; a deposit, i.e. pledging; fellowship.

h8668.definition: or תְּשֻׁעָה; from {{h7768}} in the sense of {{h3467}}; rescue (literal or figurative, persons, national or spiritual); deliverance, help, safety, salvation, victory.

h8669.definition: from {{h7783}} in the original sense of stretching out after; a longing; desire.

h8670.definition: from {{h7788}} in the sense of arrival; a gift; present.

h8672.definition: or (masculine) תִּשְׁעָה; perhaps from {{h8159}} through the idea of a turn to the next or full number ten; nine or (ordinal) ninth; nine (  -teen,   -teenth, -th).

h8674.definition: of foreign derivation; Tattenai, a Persian; Tatnai.
